                            <span class="text-base font-medium leading-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Accessible mathematics via <a href="https://www.mathjax.org/" class="underline hover:no-underline">MathJaX</a></span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex space-x-3">
                            <!-- Icon -->
                            <svg class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 text-purple-500 dark:text-purple-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
                            <span class="text-base font-medium leading-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Print, braille, and eBook support</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="mb-8 font-light lg:text-xl">
                        Create documents with universal design in mind, thanks to PreTeXt.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <img 
                    class="hidden w-full mb-4 rounded-lg lg:mb-0 lg:flex" 
                    src="https://aimath.org/~farmer/braille/braille_bubble.jpg" 
                    alt="braille mathematics">
            </div>
            <!-- Row -->
            <div class="items-center gap-8 lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 xl:gap-16">
                <%= image_tag "editor-screenshot.png", class: "hidden w-full mb-4 rounded-lg lg:mb-0 lg:flex", alt: "PreTeXt.Plus editor screenshot" %>
                <div class="text-gray-600 sm:text-lg dark:text-gray-400">
                    <h2 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
                        Getting started with PreTeXt has never been easier! 
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mb-8 font-light lg:text-xl">
                        With PreTeXt.Plus, there's no installs or GitHub accounts required: simply
                        log in and start writing. Click "Share" when you're done to create a
                        <a href="https://pretext.plus/projects/80f500c1-6c26-40f5-8ab1-e9effaf53547/share"
                           class="underline hover:no-underline hover:text-gray-400 hover:dark:text-gray-300">
                           public link</a>
                        to your accessible scholarly document!
                    </p>
                    <!-- List -->
                    <ul role="list" class="pt-8 space-y-5 border-t border-gray-200 my-7 dark:border-gray-700">
                        <li class="flex space-x-3">
                            <!-- Icon -->
                            <svg class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 text-purple-500 dark:text-purple-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
                            <span class="text-base font-medium leading-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
                                Write and preview your work in your web browser
                            </span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex space-x-3">
